\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=196086\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:423:\"<p>Looking for a simple way to view page source? Anyone can access a web page’s code by using the view page source method. And there are some good reasons why this can be useful in SEO. In this article, you’ll&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-view-page-source/\">How to View Page Source: See Any Web Page’s HTML Code (Plus: SEO Uses)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27780:\"<p>Looking for a simple way to view page source? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyone can access a web page’s code by using the view page source method. And there are some good reasons why this can be useful in SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, you’ll learn easy ways to view page source and some practical uses for doing so.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-whats-the-source-code-of-a-web-page\">What&#8217;s the Source Code of a Web Page?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-view-page-source-in-google-chrome\">How to View Page Source in Google Chrome</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-using-line-wrap-and-searching-code\">How to Use Line Wrap and Search Code</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-use-chrome-developer-tools-to-view-source-code\">How to Use Chrome Developer Tools to View Page Source</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-common-uses-for-view-page-source\">Common Uses for View Page Source</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-optimize-meta-tags-with-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Optimize Meta Tags with All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a><ul></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-whats-the-source-code-of-a-web-page\">What&#8217;s the Source Code of a Web Page?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Web pages are code files. And websites are collections of code files organized into folders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This code provides the format, style, and interactivity for the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example,</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>HTML provides formatting such as headings and paragraphs.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CSS provides styling, including colors and layout.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>JavaScript provides interactive elements like pop-ups.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Browsers instantly load and interpret these code files, rendering a visible web page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyone can view the source code of a website. Marketers and web developers are among those who use “view page source.” </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use it too for some simple SEO checks.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-view-page-source-in-google-chrome\">How to View Page Source in Google Chrome</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ll use <a href=\"https://www.google.com/chrome/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Google Chrome</a> for our example since it has the largest market share of any browser. And the keyboard shortcuts we’ll share for Chrome also work for most other browsers, including Apple Safari and Brave.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several ways to view a web page’s code in Chrome. Here are 3 listed with the quickest method first.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-method-1-keyboard-shortcut\">Method 1: Keyboard shortcut</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Mac: <strong>⌘</strong> + option + u</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Windows/Linux: Ctrl + U</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-method-2-right-click-select\">Method 2: Right-Click, Select</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Right-click</strong> on a web page. (On a Macbook, press the touchpad with both fingers.)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Select <strong>View Page Source</strong> from the pop-up window that appears.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-method-3-apple-app-menu\">Method 3: Apple App Menu</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>With Chrome open, navigate to the Apple App Menu and select <strong>View. </strong>From that drop-down menu, select <strong>Developer </strong><strong>»</strong><strong> View Source</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-using-line-wrap-and-searching-code\">Use Line Wrap and Search Code</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When the code page opens in a new tab, tick the box marked “<strong>line wrap</strong>” at the upper left. This will ensure you don&#8217;t have to scroll horizontally to view the code.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"441\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/1-view-page-source-line-wrap-1024x441.png\" alt=\"view page source line wrap tick box\" class=\"wp-image-196090\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/1-view-page-source-line-wrap-1024x441.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/1-view-page-source-line-wrap-300x129.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/1-view-page-source-line-wrap-768x331.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/1-view-page-source-line-wrap-600x259.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/1-view-page-source-line-wrap-139x60.png 139w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/1-view-page-source-line-wrap-209x90.png 209w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/1-view-page-source-line-wrap.png 1434w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use <strong>⌘ </strong>+ f to open a search box for the code.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-use-chrome-developer-tools-to-view-source-code\">How to Use Chrome Developer Tools to View Page Source</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to seeing a single page of source code, you can access Chrome developer tools from any web page to get more detailed code information. Web designers and developers use these tools. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>To access Chrome Developer Tools, use Chrome to navigate to a web page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then use the appropriate keyboard shortcut:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Mac: ⌘ + option + i</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Windows/Linux: F12 or Control + Shift + I</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>That will open a new window in the same browser tab, revealing the code behind the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"464\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-1024x464.png\" alt=\"chrome dev tools window\" class=\"wp-image-196092\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-1024x464.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-300x136.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-768x348.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-1536x695.png 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-2048x927.png 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-600x272.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-133x60.png 133w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/2-chrome-developer-tools-example2-199x90.png 199w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This view displays CSS and JavaScript event listeners, among other things.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tip: All major web browsers, including Mozilla Firefox and Microsoft Edge, offer a “dev tools” window, and the same Chrome shortcut works for these.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-common-uses-for-view-page-source\">Common Uses for View Page Source</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are 2 common reasons non-developers want to see the source code of a page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One is to check guest post backlinks. And the other is curiosity: to see what meta tags look like in HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-use-1-check-guest-post-backlinks\">Use 1: Check Guest Post Backlinks</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Backlinks, links from other sites to yours, are a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/referring-domains-vs-backlinks-seo/#aioseo-what-are-backlinks\">ranking factor</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A common way websites get backlinks is by writing guest posts for other sites in return for a link. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This backlink strategy helps individuals elevate their online presence and communicate expertise.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s important to check the code for every single link you get, though. Why? Sometimes a site owner will accidentally add a link attribute, like &#8220;sponsored” or “nofollow,” which will negate any SEO value.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These link attributes, also called tags, <strong>can only be seen in the page&#8217;s source code</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"211\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-nofollow-attribute-1024x211.png\" alt=\"nofollow attribute example in view page source window\" class=\"wp-image-196094\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-nofollow-attribute-1024x211.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-nofollow-attribute-300x62.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-nofollow-attribute-768x158.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-nofollow-attribute-600x124.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-nofollow-attribute-190x39.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-nofollow-attribute-437x90.png 437w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/3-nofollow-attribute.png 1389w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>An example of a “nofollow” attribute in a link.</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-how-to-check-html-for-link-attributes-method-1\">How to Check HTML for Link Attributes: Method 1</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Navigate to the page that is linked to yours.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Right-click on any area of the page.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Select “View Page Source.”</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The HTML code for the page will open in a new window.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Search the anchor text and check the surrounding link for <strong>nofollow</strong>, <strong>sponsored</strong>, or <strong>UGC</strong> attributes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As an example, we’ll use a ReadWrite.com article.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Scrolling to the bottom of this article, we see the guest author’s bio includes a link back to his website, Ditto Transcripts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"408\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-readwrite-bio-ben-walker-1024x408.png\" alt=\"readwrite author bio\" class=\"wp-image-196096\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-readwrite-bio-ben-walker-1024x408.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-readwrite-bio-ben-walker-300x120.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-readwrite-bio-ben-walker-768x306.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-readwrite-bio-ben-walker-600x239.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-readwrite-bio-ben-walker-150x60.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-readwrite-bio-ben-walker-226x90.png 226w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/4-readwrite-bio-ben-walker.png 1357w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Right-click anywhere on the page and select <strong>View Page Source</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That will open the HTML code for the page in a new tab. (Remember to tick the “line wrap” box.) </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, you can search the page for “Ditto Transcripts.” This is what we see.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"169\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link-1024x169.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-196122\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link-1024x169.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link-300x50.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link-768x127.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link-1536x254.png 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link-600x99.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link-190x31.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link-545x90.png 545w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/view-page-source-for-link.png 1865w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The link is a “dofollow” link, which is optimal for SEO. Notice the lack of any nofollow, sponsored, or UGC attributes in the link code.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-how-to-check-html-for-link-attributes-method-2\">How to Check HTML for Link Attributes: Method 2</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also access the link code by using Chrome Developer Tools. However, be aware that this tool displays more detailed code, which could be confusing to beginners.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s how to check a link using Chrome Dev Tools.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Navigate to the page that is linked to yours.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Right-click on the backlink.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Select <strong>Inspect</strong> from the small pop-up that appears.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open Chrome Developer Tools.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Conveniently, this action will highlight the link (in blue), so you know exactly where to look.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here we’ll use the same ReadWrite.com as our example.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To view the link’s code, we’ll right-click on it and select “Inspect” from the pop-up.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"572\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-1024x572.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-196117\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-1024x572.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-300x168.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-768x429.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-1536x859.png 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-2048x1145.png 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-600x335.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-107x60.png 107w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/open-chrome-developer-tools-1-161x90.png 161w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Selecting “Inspect” will cause Chrome Developer Tools to open. The link will be highlighted in blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"544\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-1024x544.png\" alt=\"chrome dev tools view page source code\" class=\"wp-image-196101\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-1024x544.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-300x159.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-768x408.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-1536x816.png 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-2048x1089.png 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-600x319.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-113x60.png 113w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/7-link-inspect-chrome-dev-tools-169x90.png 169w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s zoom in on that highlighted portion.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"186\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-1024x186.png\" alt=\"chrome developer tools html code source example\" class=\"wp-image-196103\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-1024x186.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-300x54.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-768x139.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-1536x279.png 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-2048x372.png 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-600x109.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-190x35.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/8-close-up-ditto-transcripts-link-496x90.png 496w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While this link code may contain things you don’t understand, you can see that there isn’t a <strong>nofollow</strong>, <strong>sponsored</strong>, or <strong>UGC</strong> tag there.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-use-2-see-what-meta-tags-look-like\">Use 2: See What Meta Tags Look Like</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The second reason non-developers may use view page source is that they’re curious to see what meta tags look like in code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may have heard that <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-title-tags/\">title tags</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-for-seo/\">meta descriptions</a> are important for SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And plugins, like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>, make it easy to edit and optimize these.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But you might wonder what these 2 meta tags look like in the source code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To find out,</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Navigate to a page.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Go to <strong>View Page Source.</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tick the &#8220;line wrap&#8221; box at the upper left.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Use <strong>⌘ + </strong>f<strong> </strong>to search for <strong>&lt;title</strong> or <strong>&lt;meta name=”description”.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example of a title tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"37\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/example-title-tag-1024x37.png\" alt=\"html title tag example\" class=\"wp-image-196105\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/example-title-tag-1024x37.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/example-title-tag-300x11.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/example-title-tag-768x28.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/example-title-tag-600x22.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/example-title-tag-190x7.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/example-title-tag-750x27.png 750w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/example-title-tag.png 1166w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And here’s the meta description for the same article.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"127\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/meta-description-example-syed-story-1024x127.png\" alt=\"html meta description example\" class=\"wp-image-196106\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/meta-description-example-syed-story-1024x127.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/meta-description-example-syed-story-300x37.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/meta-description-example-syed-story-768x95.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/meta-description-example-syed-story-600x74.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/meta-description-example-syed-story-190x24.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/meta-description-example-syed-story-727x90.png 727w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/meta-description-example-syed-story.png 1324w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-optimize-meta-tags-with-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Optimize Meta Tags with All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing these meta tags is easy with the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO) plugin</a> for WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And you won&#8217;t need to view the page source to check meta tags.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png\" alt=\"aioseo homepage\" class=\"wp-image-140989\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-768x364.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-600x284.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-127x60.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage-190x90.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/aioseo-homepage.png 1260w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This established plugin has thousands of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/testimonials/\">5-star reviews</a> on WordPress.org and over 3 million users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While it’s easy for beginners to use AIOSEO, it delivers pro results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can download All in One SEO <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll see a <strong>preview</strong> of your title and meta description in Google Search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1000\" height=\"226\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-snippet-preview.png\" alt=\"aioseo snippet preview\" class=\"wp-image-196109\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-snippet-preview.png 1000w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-snippet-preview-300x68.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-snippet-preview-768x174.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-snippet-preview-600x136.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-snippet-preview-190x43.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-snippet-preview-398x90.png 398w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And you get easy ways to optimize these tags, such as keeping your meta description within a set length.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1007\" height=\"278\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-meta-description.png\" alt=\"aioseo meta description\" class=\"wp-image-196108\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-meta-description.png 1007w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-meta-description-300x83.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-meta-description-768x212.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-meta-description-600x166.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-meta-description-190x52.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-meta-description-326x90.png 326w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, All in One SEO provides recommendations for improving the SEO of your individual web pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"462\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-seo-recommendations-1024x462.jpg\" alt=\"aioseo seo recommendations\" class=\"wp-image-196111\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-seo-recommendations-1024x462.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-seo-recommendations-300x135.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-seo-recommendations-768x346.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-seo-recommendations-600x270.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-seo-recommendations-133x60.jpg 133w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-seo-recommendations-200x90.jpg 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/aioseo-seo-recommendations.jpg 1260w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Other benefits include</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Easy setup for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/local-business-seo-for-a-single-location/\">local SEO</a> (for small businesses).</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Recommendations on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/using-the-focus-keyphrase-to-analyze-your-content/\">focus keyword</a> use.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Turn your pages into <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-rich-snippets-to-wordpress/\">rich snippets</a> with a few button clicks.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"564\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-1024x564.jpg\" alt=\"rich snippets example\" class=\"wp-image-183115\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-1024x564.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-300x165.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-768x423.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-1536x846.jpg 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-2048x1127.jpg 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-600x330.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-109x60.jpg 109w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/leather-jacket-rich-snippet-163x90.jpg 163w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Rich snippets stand out in search results and get more click-throughs</em>.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-qa-on-view-page-source\">Q&amp;A on View Page Source</h2>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-how-do-i-view-page-source-in-safari\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">How do I view page source in Safari?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>To view page source in Safari, right-click on the page and choose <strong>Show Page Source</strong>. Or, in the browser menu, select <strong>Develop </strong>» <strong>Show Page Source</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using <strong>Option + Command </strong>(⌘)<strong> + U</strong> will open the Developer Tools window.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-how-do-i-find-the-html-and-css-code-of-a-website\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">How do I find the HTML and CSS code of a website?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>There are several ways to find the HTML and CSS code of a website. To find the HTML you can use various view page source methods <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-view-page-source/#aioseo-how-to-view-page-source-in-google-chrome\" title=\"\">outlined here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To see the HTML and CSS code you can use the Developer Tools feature in your web browser.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also find the clickable CSS code file(s) for a website in the head element of the HTML.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-whats-next\">What’s Next?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you understand how to view a page’s source code and why people use it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to learn more about the role of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/referring-domains-vs-backlinks-seo/\">backlinks in SEO</a> and get insights into <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-are-paid-links-in-seo/\">paid links</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-guide/\">link building</a>. And don&#8217;t forget to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/lead-generation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">capture those leads</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube channel</a> for SEO tutorials. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-view-page-source/\">How to View Page Source: See Any Web Page’s HTML Code (Plus: SEO Uses)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-view-page-source/feed/\";s:7:\"a